ACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>12/3/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>7:59:42 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathwhatisapaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Paladins(outside the context of EQ)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Greetings all, <BR>  <BR> I would like to get your thoughts on the following post.  I have been fascinated with the idea of Paladins for many years now.  In high school, at the arcades during lunch, you would see PAL in the top scores with the game Golden Axe. :-) Among MANY others.  I have read hundreds of books and became a student of Medieval History at University of Western Ontario.   I am a member of the SCA and two to three times weekly, I strap on a suit of Armour and beat up(or try to) a great many Knights in the Land.   <BR>  <BR> There are some obvious ideals of the Paladin.  Many of us have these ideals set in our hearts and minds.  Are there REAL examples of a Paladin?  My PASSION is Fourteenth Century England.  I have studied as much as I can, and there are still millions of books out there to research.  Here are some examples : <BR>  <BR> Edward the Black Prince is a prime example of a real Paladin.  He was incredibly dedicated to the Church and gave away much wealth to them.  He was a courtly gentleman who respected women and men.  On the battlefield, he was unstoppable.  He was the commander for many of England's &quot;miracle&quot; victories in the Hundred Year's War.  At Crecy and Poitiers, he won battles that were almost impossible.  He was responsible for great strife and destruction of the French countryside, but, he had thousands of men to keep happy.  I am not justifying his actions, but the &quot;enemy&quot;(French) saw him as a monster. <BR>  <BR> Henry V - The battle of Agincourt was a great battle.  Many people died fighting for their beliefs.  Rent Henry V with Kenneth Branagh.  Now HE is a Paladin. :-) <BR>  <BR> Lancelot, Galahad, etc.  - The Knights of the Round Table have had a great influence on the development of the Paladin.  When Lancelot betrayed his King, you see a Fallen Paladin.   <BR>  <BR> Charlemagne - The founding &quot;Father&quot; of Paladins, his was the first literary mention of the Great Warriors.  <BR>  <BR> Joan of Arc - a great example of a Warrior in a Higher Cause.   <BR>  <BR> What is a Paladin?  On one hand, Edward the Black Prince was a Saviour to the English but a scourge on the French.   <BR> What do you think makes a Paladin?   <BR>  <BR> If I ever finish my degree, I can see my Thesis forming now. :-) What a load of random thoughts, please respond and feel free to comment. <BR>  <BR> Varrus Aurelius <BR>  <BR> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Caerwynn</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>12/6/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>2:24:33 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathwhatisapaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Paladins in RL</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My thoughts on what makes a Paladin in real life is somewhat similar as my thoughts to what one in Game is. <BR> You mention the Black Prince Edward I agree he was a true Holy warrior. He fought for his country and his God. The French reviled him because he was the enemy. I am pretty sure that the other Knights of both sides judged him to be a great holy warrior and had respect for him. <BR> El Cid though not mentioned by you. I consider a Paladin also. He fought for his country and ideals above all else. Not letting anything stand in his way of his ideals, except of course his belief in God. <BR> Richard the Lionheart was a Paladin he fought and endured many hardships but never lost faith in his God or his men. <BR> One more though this one is not usually thought of in warrior context and that would be Ghandi. <BR> Though he did not physically fight he was put to the test for his beliefs in his God and Ideals and he did not waver in either. He is one whom I consider to be a True Holy Warrior fighting (in his fashion) for his people, His God and His ideals without using violence a true test of Bravery. <BR>  <BR> So in my mind a Paladin is one who will stand by his Beliefs and Ideals even if faced with immenent death. A true holy warrior is not only one who fights, lives and dies for his God but also one who fights, lives and dies for his ideals. </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://server5.ezboard.com/uvarrusaurelius.showPublicProfile>Varrus Aurelius</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>12/7/99</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>8:14:46 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathwhatisapaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Paladins in RL</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ah! <BR>  <BR> Great post!  Thanks for the input.  I agree with all of the people you feel are deserving of recognition.  Anyone else come to mind?  I SHOULD have thought of El Cid and Richard. :-)  I was hard at work though, hehe. <BR>  <BR> </font><P>Varrus Aurelius<BR>
