</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thoreth>Thoreth</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>8/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>9:43:56 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathwhatisapaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=7><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A><BR><img src=http://facelink.snap.com/edit/raw/rawimage/36/1074736.jpg?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Musashi was Re: Paladins(outside the context of EQ</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'm not really sure if I'd consider Musashi Miyamoto to be a paladin.  While he did have a code of ethics, it was more like a &quot;Win at All Costs&quot; code.  While Paladins are, in many ways, supposed to be the warrior ideal, they're also supposed to be holy warriors.<br>
<br>
